reviews.review_text:
Missing Encores Superb Bertha Remaster cleans-up bass and kick nicely and there is no appreciable hiss.

Was lucky enough to witness the band one in spades that night.

There some cuts and drop outs in the recording and there's some lapses in concentration on the band's part, but overall, it's the epitome of liquid fire GD at their shredding best. The entire second set is resplendent in urban atmospheric glory and evanescent in display. Truckin' and Around are major skullf**ks.

Enjoy.
A substantial improvement over the other source for this date.  You really get the feeling you are in a hall with this version.  I like it.
I agree This sounds better.  5 stars for better.
dats it bast here. u no it.
12-27-77 Incredible both in performance and sound quality. Thanks Jay.

Fix for LL Dropouts I agree with other reviewers that this is the cleanest version (as the Bertha usually is). However, to correct for the dropouts in LL from 1:11 to 1:15, substitute the LL > Supp from the "Anonymous" SBD (thank you, JCotsman). This isn't an AUD patch--the dropouts just aren't on this SBD. Unfortunately, the Gans-Redbeard version has the same dropouts.

If public uploads were possible, I'd add my patched version. If anyone who has access wants the files: gratefuldiver11@gmail.com.
